FBIS4-56964 "drlat091_m_94011" FBIS-LAT-94-091 Daily Report 9 May 1994 Brazil Bahia PSDB Decides To Support Lula's Candidacy Bahia PSDB Decides To Support Lula's Candidacy PY1005224294 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 9 May 94 Section 1 p 6 PY1005224294 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO Portuguese BFN [Article by Felipe Farias] [Excerpt] The Bahia State branch of the Brazilian Social Democracy Party [PSDB] has decided to support Workers Party presidential candidate Luis Inacio Lula da Silva. The decision was made during the 8 May convention that officially nominated former Minister Jutahy Magalhaes, Jr., as the party's gubernatorial candidate for Bahia, Deputy Sergio Gaudenzi as vice gubernatorial candidate, and Waldir Pires as candidate for the Senate. The position of the Bahia branch of the PSDB is deemed irreversible. Jutahy Magalhaes, Jr. said: "The decision has been made. Everywhere I go I say that my presidential candidate is Lula. We have already reported our decision to the party and to Fernando Henrique Cardoso." [passage omitted]
